# Copy into `.env` (or merge) for `prepare_ingestion.py --finetune`
# API key resolution order: FINETUNE_API_KEY → OPENROUTER_API_KEY → OPENAI_API_KEY
#
# FINETUNE_API_KEY=
# FINETUNE_API_BASE=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
# FINETUNE_MODEL=google/gemini-2.5-flash-lite

# Required for finetune: instruction prompt (multiline OK inside double quotes)
FINETUNE_PROMPT="You are cleaning web-scraped markdown for retrieval (RAG) and fine-tuning.\n\nGoals:\n- Remove boilerplate: cookie banners, subscribe widgets, repeated nav/footer blocks, social share rows, and empty decorative lines.\n- Keep all substantive facts: names, dates, rules, links that carry meaning, tables, lists, and headings.\n- Normalize headings and lists; fix broken line breaks inside sentences where obvious.\n- Do not invent facts or URLs. If the source is noisy but readable, condense without losing information.\n- Output plain Markdown only. No preamble, no code fences around the whole document, no 'Here is the cleaned version'."

# Optional OpenRouter attribution headers
# FINETUNE_HTTP_REFERER=https://yoursite.example
# FINETUNE_X_TITLE=prepare_ingestion
